  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a retrospective database review of primary care appointments of patients'
      charts with new diagnoses of hypertension.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Compare the degree of blood pressure control of patients with stage 1 (BP &lt; 130/80 mmHg) and
      stage 2 hypertension (BP &gt; 20/10 mm Hg above goal BP) before and after the release of the
      Seventh report of Joint Committee on Prevention, Detection, Evaluation and Treatment of High
      Blood Pressure (JNC 7) recommendations.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
